Britain and the Sea is a British documentary television series presented and written by David Dimbleby that was first broadcast on BBC One on 17 November 2013. The series was made in partnership with National Maritime Museum and explores Britain's maritime heritage.


David Dimbleby takes to his wooden sailing boat to explore Britain's rich maritime heritage






1/4 David Dimbleby sails the south west coast of England in his own sailing boat.

2/4 David continues his voyage round Britain, sailing along the south east coast.

3/4 David Dimbleby traces the crucial importance of the sea to Britain's trade.

4/4 David Dimbleby explores how the sea emerged as a source of pleasure
